Note:  This is very early development code.  Therefore it is still very, very ugly ;)

ld-decode takes the raw RF data signal (captured using cxadc) and converts it into a raw composite video signal.  audio is not decoded yet.

ntsc-decode takes that, time base corrects it, and decodes the color using a 1D comb filter, which provides mixed results

to run:  

./ld-decode [file] > [file].ld 
./tbc [file.ld] > [file].tbc
./ntsc-decode [file].tbc > [file].rgb

or pipelined:

./ld file.raw [start] [length] | ./tbc - | ./ntsc - > file.rgb

to view ld-decode output: display -size 1820x512 -depth 16 gray:ldplant.ld 
to view ntsc-decode output: display -size 1536x480 -depth 16 rgb:ldplant.rgb
use this command line to make it a .jpg:  convert -size 1536x480 -depth 16 rgb:ntscbar.rgb -resize 45%x100% ntscbar.jpg

To convert from .rgb to high quality .mp4:

avconv -f rawvideo -pix_fmt rgb48 -s 1536x480 -i file.rgb -qscale 3 -s 720x480 file.mp4

